<HEADLINE> Mercury 84, Miracle 77  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Jennifer Gillom scored 28 points on 10-of-12
shooting and grabbed six rebounds to lead the Phoenix Mercury to an
84-77 victory over the Orlando Miracle on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Mercury set a franchise record for field goal percentage,
going 29-of-51 (56.9 percent). The previous record was 55 percent
in an 80-62 victory at Houston on June 3.
</P>
<P>
   Tonya Edwards scored 12 points and Brandy Reed added 11 for
Phoenix (18-10), which has won four of its last five games.
</P>
<P>
   Adrienne Johnson led Orlando with 24 points and Shannon Johnson
added 15.
</P>
<P>
   The loss was the sixth straight for the Miracle (14-14) and
eighth in their last nine games. It is the first time since June 22
that Orlando has been at the .500 mark.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando cut a 10-point deficit to 66-64 with 4:10 left. Gillom
then made a basket and a 3-pointer as the Mercury went on a 7-0 run
and pulled away.
</P>
<P>
   The Mercury also set a team record for field goal percentage in
a first half, going 17-of-25 (68 percent) in taking a 41-34 lead.
The old record of 63.3 percent was also set June 3.
</P>
