<HEADLINE> Fire 54, Sol 50  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Sophia Witherspoon scored 24 points and
Tully Bevilaqua hit a go-ahead pair of free throws in the final
minute, lifting the Portland Fire to a 54-50 win over the expansion
Miami Sol on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Bevilaqua was fouled by Michelle Black on a fast break with 43
seconds left and hit both shots to give Portland a 51-50 lead.
Miami did not score on its next three possessions.
</P>
<P>
   Sheri Sam scored 23 to lead the Sol, who outrebounded the Fire
34-17 led by Marlies Askamp's 10, but shot just 33 percent from the
field.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (10-18) went on a 10-5 run to start the second half,
taking a 39-31 lead as the Fire went 4:37 without scoring.
</P>
<P>
   The Fire (10-18) cut into the lead as Witherspoon hit a pair of
3-pointers to bring Portland within 42-39. Sylvia Crawley then
banked a layup in with 7:18 left, and Witherspoon's pair of free
throws a minute later gave Portland its first lead since the first
minute of the half.
</P>
<P>
   Sam countered with a short jumper to beat the shot clock, and
Black rebounded Sam's miss and hit a layup with 4:10 left to give
Miami a 46-44 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Crawley then hit one of two free throws and DeMya Walker added a
pair to give Portland a 49-48 lead.
</P>
<P>
   After Black hit a pair from the free-throw line with 1:19 left,
Michelle Marciniak forced a Miami turnover, setting up Bevilaqua's
free throws.
</P>
<P>
   Witherspoon went 8-for-9 from the line and Walker hit all four
of her free throws.
</P>
