<HEADLINE> Search teams look for canoeist missing on the Delaware River  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   UPPER BLACK EDDY, Pa. (AP) - Rescue boats and divers searched
without success Tuesday for a missing canoeist whose dog and
equipment were found on the boat Monday, floating on the Delaware
River without him.
</P>
<P>
   The effort Tuesday turned up no sign of the victim after the
initial search Monday night was cut short by a thunderstorm, said a
spokesman for the Upper Black Eddy Fire Co. The search will likely
resume this morning, he said.
</P>
<P>
   A witness reported seeing a man without a shirt in a motorized
canoe on the river north of Milford in the afternoon, said Mike
Sciss, deputy chief of the Upper Black Eddy Fire Co. By the time it
reached the Milford Bridge to Hunderdon County, N.J., the man was
gone, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Another witness reported seeing a man getting out of a canoe
less than a half-mile above the bridge, but no sign of him was
found on land.
</P>
<P>
   A fishing license with a man's name was recovered from the boat,
along with two coolers, several changes of clothes, maps, a
lifejacket and some empty beer cans, Schiss said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It looks like he started up north,'' Sciss said. ''There's a
lot of gear; he may have been out for a couple of days.''
</P>
<P>
   The dog, part German shepherd, was so agitated that firfighters
could not get it out of the canoe, until officials from the
Hunterdon County SPCA came to restrain it.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
