<HEADLINE> Actor Graves Celebrates Milestones  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Actor Peter Graves is celebrating two
milestones rarely seen in Hollywood -- a half-century in front of
the camera and 50 years of marriage.
</P>
<P>
   The A&AMP;E ''Biography'' host began his career opposite Rory
Calhoun in the 1950 film ''Rogue River,'' and his career continued
through an eight-year run on TV's ''Mission Impossible'' and now
''Biography.''
</P>
<P>
   Graves, 74, called his wife Joan a steadying influence. ''I hate
to think what would ever have happened to me without her good
guidance and affection through certain times.''
</P>
<P>
   After several movies, Graves accepted a part on the series
''Fury'' in what was then the fairly new medium of television.
</P>
<P>
   ''It seemed to be very clear to motion picture producers that
television was beneath contempt,'' Graves said. ''But there were a
lot of actors who had been free-lance actors a long time and knew
it was a dangerous business. The idea of a television series that
guaranteed 39 films a year was very attractive.''
</P>
</TEXT>
