<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Diabetes Drug Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- An Aug. 1 story on the Food and Drug
Administration's approval of a new Bristol-Myers Squibb diabetes
drug, Glucovance, incorrectly identified the drug's makeup.
Glucovance is a combination of another diabetes drug made by the
company, Glucophage, and the generic diabetes pill glyburide.
</P>
<P>
   The story incorrectly said it was Glucophage and metformin,
which is the generic name of Glucophage.
