<HEADLINE> 17 of 18 Westchester beaches to reopen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) - Seventeen of Westchester's 18 closed
beaches will be reopened for swimming on Thursday, the county
Health Department said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The beaches were closed because heavy rains last week swamped
five sewage pumping stations on the shore of Long Island Sound.
</P>
<P>
   Only the Harbor Island Beach in Mamaroneck, which has been shut
down all season, will remain closed, said department spokeswoman
Valerie Goldstein.
</P>
<P>
   Rain water funneling into the sewage system overwhelmed pump
stations in Larchmont, Mamaroneck and New Rochelle. A a result,
some of the sewage entered the sound, diluted and chlorinated but
not otherwise treated, Goldstein said.
</P>
<P>
   These beaches will reopen:
</P>
<P>
   -In New Rochelle, Beckwith Pointe, Davenport Yacht Club, Echo
Bay Yacht Club, Glen Island, Greentree Club, Hudson Park, Marina's
Edge, New Rochelle Rowing Club, Sans Souci, Surf Club and VIP Club.
</P>
<P>
   -In Larchmont, at Larchmont Manor Park and Larchmont Shore Club.
</P>
<P>
   -In Mamaroneck, Beach Point Club, Mamaroneck Beach Yacht and
Cabana Club, Shore Acres Point Club and Orienta Club.
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Westchester Health Department,
http://www.westchestergov.com/health
</P>
</TEXT>
