<HEADLINE> Man discovered burned to death in bed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HOBOKEN, N.J. (AP) - Police were questioning a female friend of
a 68-year-old disabled man found burned to death in his bed
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Harry Dennis, 68, was burned over approximately 80 percent of
his body, said Deputy First Assistant Hudson County Prosecutor
Edward DeFazio.
</P>
<P>
   A Meals-on-Wheels employee who arrived to deliver food to Dennis
on Wednesday found Dennis' body and his female friend in his
apartment, DeFazio said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman told police that Dennis died Wednesday by carelessly
igniting a cigarette after applying rubbing alcohol on himself,
DeFazio said.
</P>
<P>
   But an autopsy that determined Dennis burned to death could not
pinpoint the time of his death, DeFazio said.
</P>
<P>
   DeFazio wouldn't call the woman a suspect and said investigators
have yet to determine whether Dennis' death was an accident or not.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis was disabled and occasionally required a wheelchair,
DeFazio said.
</P>
