<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-02 20:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Officer accused of trying to entice a child to engage in sexual activity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) - A New York City police officer who
allegedly sent a picture of himself in a police cruiser to someone
he thought was a 14-year-old girl was charged Wednesday with trying
to entice a child to engage in sexual activity.
</P>
<P>
   Philip Amatulli, 25, an officer since April 15, 1997, was taken
into custody at his Bronxville home on federal charges that he used
interstate communications to commit the crime. He was suspended
without pay, police said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors alleged that he used Internet chat rooms to try to
meet young girls and then persuade them to have sexual relations
with him.
</P>
<P>
   Amatulli appeared in White Plains before U.S. Magistrate Judge
Lisa M. Smith, who released him on $150,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're confident that when all these surrounding facts and
circumstances about this case come to light that my client will be
vindicated,'' said his lawyer, Rene Medina. A prosecutor in the
case did not immediately return a telephone message.
</P>
<P>
   Smith also ordered Amatulli to surrender his weapons, barred him
from using the Internet and ordered him to have no unsupervised
contact with minors.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors said a search warrant executed at his home on July
20 found that Amatulli had stored hundreds of images of child
pornography on his home computer.
</P>
<P>
   The arrest resulted after an investigation that began when
Amatulli allegedly established Internet contact with a person he
believed to be a 14-year-old girl living in the Washington D.C.
area.
</P>
<P>
   The person, prosecutors said in court papers, was actually a
U.S. Customs Service special agent.
</P>
<P>
   A complaint filed in U.S. District Court in White Plains said
Amatulli tried to entice the agent during several Internet and
telephone conversations to engage in sexual intercourse.
</P>
<P>
   The complaint alleged that Amatulli claimed he had recently met
a 12-year-old girl over the Internet and had sex with her.
</P>
<P>
   When the Customs agent told him she had reservations about
having intercourse, Amatulli allegedly promised she would not get
pregnant and said he would send a picture of himself in his uniform
and his police car to make her feel more at ease, according to the
complaint.
</P>
<P>
   Later, Amatulli used e-mail to send the agent two pictures of
himself in a New York City police uniform and seated in a New York
City police car.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-08-02-00 2003 </TRAILER>
