<HEADLINE> Arabian Light Wins Graduation Stake  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Arabian Light made it two wins in as many
lifetime starts Wednesday, breezing to a five-length victory over
Stocks Are Rising in the $125,000 Graduation Stakes for 2-year-olds
at Del Mar.
</P>
<P>
   Ridden by David Flores and carrying 117 pounds, Arabian Light
covered 5&AMP;frac12; furlongs in 1:03 4-5 and, as the 3-5 favorite, paid
$3.20, $2.40 and $2.10.
</P>
<P>
   The win was worth $75,000, raising Arabian Light's career
earnings to $100,800. The son of Fly So Free won his only previous
start, at Hollywood Park in June.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks Are Rising, an 18-1 long shot ridden by Laffit Pincay
Jr., and carrying 114 pounds, crossed the finish line 1&AMP;frac12; lengths
ahead of Rocky's Crew and returned $6.60 and $2.60.
</P>
<P>
   Rocky's Crew, ridden by Alex Solis and carrying 117 pounds, was
a neck in front of Good Cop Bad Cop at the wire and paid $2.40 to
show. Solis rode four winners earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
   Shining Nuggets finished fifth and Cool Composure was sixth and
last in the 49th running of the race, contested previously at six
furlongs. Nonconnah Creek, Oh Really, Slew Has A Message and Tidal
Prince were scratched.
