videotape of the session with pitching guru Billy Connors. ''I
realize I need to work on other things,'' said Cone, ordered to
Florida last weekend by owner George Steinbrenner. ''You don't have
time to work like this in the major leagues.'' Cone, who is 1-10
and winless since April 28, could leave Friday to rejoin the
Yankees. ... Yankees manager Joe Torre wanted to find out the
status of Cone and Orlando Hernandez before deciding on his weekend
rotation. Hernandez, at Tampa on a rehab assignment, has been on
the disabled list since July 14 because of discomfort in his right
elbow and mild back spasms. ... New York's medical staff is
examining Adrian Hernandez, who may have torn knee ligaments
pitching in the minor leagues earlier this week. ''El Duquecito,''
no relation to ''El Duque,'' signed with the Yankees earlier this
year after defecting from Cuba.
