Schmidt had inflammation but no tear in his right rotator cuff.
Schmidt, the Pirates' opening day starter, hasn't pitched since
early June and, because of latest setback, may not pitch again this
season. ... The Pirates finished 6-6 on their longest homestand of
the season. They play 16 of their next 19 on the road through
August 23, returning home only to play Arizona on Aug. 11-13. ...
OF Adrian Brown (hamstring) is 2-for-9 in three games on a
rehabilitation assignment at Triple-A Nashville. ... Francisco
Cordova, who starts Thursday night in San Francisco, was 0-2 with a
10.80 ERA against the Giants last season and is 2-4 with a 6.08 ERA
against them in nine career appearances. ... 1B Kevin Young,
considered one of the NL's top defensive first basemen two years
ago, committed his 16th error Wednesday. He has 39 errors the last
two seasons; the last major league 1B with more than 40 errors in
consecutive seasons was the Pirates' Donn Clendenon, who had 52 in
1965 and 1966. Young blames knee surgery that he believes has cost
him a step and restricted his range and mobility.
