hadn't gotten in the way. ''I didn't sleep last night I was so
ticked,'' Gonzalez said. ''If that happened in Boston with the Red
Sox fans, that guy would have needed a serious police escort out of
there.'' ... RHP Todd Stottlemyre has thrown for three days without
any pain in his shoulder. It's the first time he's thrown since he
went on the DL June 26 with tendinitis in the right elbow. The
Diamondbacks say he could be back by September, but he hopes it's
sooner.
