<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 31 Arrested in Colombia Drug Bust  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) -- U.S. and Colombian agents on Wednesday
arrested 31 people alleged to be members of a narcotics ring
exporting cocaine and heroin to the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P>
   In pre-dawn raids of 40 homes in six different cities on
Colombia's Caribbean coast, agents from the U.S. Drug Enforcement
Administration and 250 Colombian anti-narcotics officials also
found an undisclosed amount of cocaine and heroin, said Luis
Ernesto Gilibert, the director of Colombia's national police force.
</P>
<P>
   Among those arrested Wednesday was Libardo Parra, the suspected
leader of the Caribbean Cartel, the group targeted by the sting,
said Gilibert, who personally oversaw the operation.
</P>
<P>
   He said the cartel used small boats and planes to export
narcotics to the United States using routes in Mexico and to Europe
via Haiti, Jamaica and Aruba.
</P>
<P>
   The raids were one of the largest anti-narcotics operations in
Colombian history and the largest since the U.S. Congress approved
a $1.3 billion aid package in July to help Colombian authorities
battle narcotics traffickers and leftists rebels.
</P>
<P>
   Gilibert said more arrests could be coming later this week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
