<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marlins 5, Astros 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Pinch-hitter Henry Rodriguez doubled in his first
at-bat for Florida, setting up Luis Castillo's two-run single in
the bottom of the ninth inning that lifted the Marlins over the
Houston Astros 5-4 Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Dave Berg singled off Marc Valdes (2-3) to start the ninth and
Rodriguez, acquired Monday from the Chicago Cubs, batted for Ramon
Castro and blooped a double.
</P>
<P>
   Jesus Sanchez pinch-ran for Rodriguez and Mike Lowell was hit by
a pitch, loading the bases with no outs. Castillo followed with a
single off Valdes' leg into center field.
</P>
<P>
   Dan Miceli (5-2) got the victory.
</P>
<P>
   Julio Lugo, starting in place of injured second baseman Craig
Biggio, had three hits for the Astros.
</P>
<P>
   Biggio tore ligaments in his left knee after getting tangled up
with Florida's Preston Wilson while taking a throw at second
Tuesday night. On Wednesday, Biggio was placed on the disabled list
for the first time in his 13-year career.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Bagwell and Lance Berkman hit consecutive home runs for
Houston. Bagwell led off the fourth with his 29th home run and
Berkman hit his 16th off Reid Cornelius. Moises Alou followed with
a double, but was stranded.
</P>
<P>
   Astros starter Wade Miller faded in the sixth with a 4-1 lead.
Wilson had an RBI grounder, and two walks loaded the bases with two
outs.
</P>
<P>
   Reliever Joe Slusarski walked Berg on four pitches, making it
4-3.
</P>
<P>
   Houston chased Cornelius in the sixth behind Tony Eusebio's
two-run double.
</P>
<P>
   Andy Fox homered in the Marlins fifth.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Astros have 12 players who weren't on their 25-man
roster on opening day. ... Houston RHP Jay Powell will begin a
rehab assignment in Round Rock on Thursday. ... Lugo started at
second base for the second time this year. He tied a career high
with three hits. ... Florida rookie RHP Brad Penny (sore shoulder)
is eligible to return from the 15-day DL Thursday. He will make at
least two rehab starts for Class A Brevard County. If all goes
well, he could make an Aug. 15 start against the Dodgers. ...
Cornelius was called for his third balk in his last three starts.
He hadn't been charged with a balk since 1995 until getting called
for two against Montreal on July 22.
</P>
</TEXT>
