<HEADLINE> Starzz 72, Lynx 62  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Jennifer Azzi had a season-high 20 points and
seven assists as the Utah Starzz beat the Minnesota Lynx 72-62
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Natalie Williams, averaging a league-leading 12.3 rebounds per
game, had 11 and scored nine points as Utah (16-12) won for the
first time in Minnesota, after losing the first three times.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx (13-15) took an 8-1 lead before the Starzz went on a
31-14 run to take a 32-22 lead at halftime. The Lynx scored just
five points in the final 10&AMP;frac12; minutes of the half.
</P>
<P>
   Utah shot 64.3 percent (9-for-14) on 3-pointers, led by Azzi
(3-for-4) and Korie Hlede (4-for-6). Hlede had 15 points and
Adrienne Goodson added 14.
</P>
<P>
   Betty Lennox, 3-for-6 on 3-pointers, had 21 points for the Lynx,
who shot 35.3 percent (6-for-17) from behind the arc. Katie Smith
added 15 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Starzz resevers outscored their Minnesota counterparts 9-1,
though the Lynx non-starters played more minutes (42-18).
</P>
</TEXT>
