<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Will Shields Signs Deal With Chiefs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIVER FALLS, Wis. (AP) -- Will Shields, who has played in the
last five Pro Bowls, accepted the Kansas City Chiefs tender offer
of a one-year $4.1 contract on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Shields, the Chiefs' franchise player, will earn the average
salary of the NFL's five highest paid offensive lineman based on
1999 salaries.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-2, 321-pound right guard was Kansas City' third-round
draft choice in 1993, and has started 111 of 112 games since.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
